                            <comment id="13739939" author="eclark" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 17:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because the fsRead and write latency mixed compaction in with normal operation those metrics were basically useless so they were culled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740022" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 18:39:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fsRead metrics are just some example.&lt;br/&gt;
The ability to provide periodic metrics update is still desirable, right ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740104" author="devaraj" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 19:50:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am tending to agree with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;. Since we have metrics for the individual get/put/etc requests, we probably don&apos;t need the FS metrics. I was discussing with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yuzhihong%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yuzhihong@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt; on whether we should retain these metrics just as an indicator of overall latencies that we see for FS operations. But that would be more than just the HStore operations (that the current fs* metrics target)...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13749220" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sat, 24 Aug 2013 01:19:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Plan to close this JIRA if there is no objection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
